As illustrated in Figure 2, the Ga(In)As and Ge are lattice matched which were confirmed by the single Bragg peak. In both HRXRD spectra, the five period InAs/GaAs QD superlattice (SL) fringe peaks are visible. The zeroth-order peak of sample A1 is buried underneath the Ga(In)As and Ge Bragg peak, but a shift of 140 arc-second is observed in sample A2, meaning that the five period InAs/GaAs QD SL is under a tensile strain from the substrate. The out-of-plane strain ε⊥ is 1.045‰, which is determined from a differentiated formulation of Bragg’s law shown as followed [17]:Figure 2
